  <discussion>Subspecies glauca, which is the most morphologically variable and most widespread
        North American taxon in Noccaea, corresponds to Thlaspi montanum var. montanum in the sense
        of P. K. Holmgren (1971) and R. C. Rollins (1993). As indicated above, that variety is a
        strictly European taxon. Subspecies glauca exhibits a wide elevational range, and one
        collection, Clements 427 (US), was made at 4350 m at the summit of Pike’s Peak,
        Colorado.</discussion>
